-- HIGHLIGHTS-Draghi comments at ECB news conference
-- 
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 08:37AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, June 5 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank cut interest rates to record lows on Thursday, imposing negative rates on its overnight depositors to cajole banks into lending more and to fight off the risk of deflation.

Following are comments by ECB President Mario Draghi at a post-meeting news conference.  FORWARD GUIDANCE "Concerning our forward guidance, the key ECB interest rates will remain at present levels for an extended period of time in view of the current outlook for inflation."